<BaseLayout title="Common Negative Prompts Explained" description="Understand common negative prompt terms and when to use them." canonicalPath="/guides/negative-prompts/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>Common Negative Prompts Explained</h1><p>Negative prompts tell the model what to avoid. Common cleanup terms include low quality, blurry, extra fingers, deformed hands, watermark, and text overlay.</p><p>Use them sparingly. Repeating the same negative term or adding a long list of unrelated problems can make the prompt harder to interpret.</p></article></BaseLayout>
